A LOW TIME PVT PILOT FLARED THE AIRCRAFT WHICH TOUCHED DOWN HARD AND 
BOUNCED. ON THE SECOND TOUCHDOWN, THE AIRCRAFT ENTERED A GROUND LOOP TO 
THE RIGHT. APPLICATION OF RIGHT BRAKE AND RUDDER DID NOT CORRECT THE 
SITUATION. THE LEFT WING AND NOSE WENT DOWN AND THE AIRCRAFT WENT OVER ONTO 
ITS BACK. THE AIRCRAFT WAS EQUIPPED WITH CONVENTIONAL LANDING GEAR. THE PILOT 
REPORTED THAT AFTER HE HAD OBTAINED A PVT PILOT CERTIFICATE ON 03/03/84 
AND HAD NOT FLOWN AFTER THAT DATE UNTIL THE DAY OF THE ACCIDENT. 
